<Base title="Latent control states · Xiaochuan Li">
  <article class="prose">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-text-dim)] font-medium mb-2">
      Project · May–Dec 2026
    </div>
    <h1>Latent control states under prompt framing</h1>
    <p class="text-[var(--color-text-muted)] italic !text-lg !mb-8">
      Mechanistic interpretability of prompt-induced behavioral shifts.
    </p>

    <p>
      <em>Detail page coming.</em> This project asks whether prompt framing–induced changes in model
      behavior correspond to causally relevant states in activation space, or merely to surface
      features that travel with the prompt. Planned methods include probing, sparse autoencoders,
      activation patching, and steering.
    </p>

    <p>
      It is the methodological complement to <a href="/research/isotrace">Isotrace</a>: behavioral
      tracing and mechanistic interpretability asking the same question from opposite ends.
    </p>
  </article>
</Base>
